\title{Degree of Field Extensions is Multiplicative}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-20}
\taxon{theorem}

\p{Let #{\LL / \kk} and #{\kk / \FF} be field extensions. Then
##{\Index{\LL}{\FF}=\Index{\LL}{\kk}\Index{\kk}{\FF}.}}

\rmk{This is also known as "the degree equation", "the tower rule", and "the tower law", since a [finite] chain of field extensions is known as a "tower of fields".}